President Obama spoke with Major General John (J.T.) Thomson, the commanding general of the 1st Cavalry Division at Fort Hood, Texas, to express his condolences to the families and friends of the soldiers who were killed in a flash flooding incident during a training exercise. The President thanked Major General Thomson and the leaders at Fort Hood for their efforts in coordinating search and recovery operations. He also acknowledged the risks that military personnel face in both peacetime and wartime operations and expressed his gratitude for their sacrifices. The President and First Lady are keeping the 1st Cavalry Division and the United States Military Academy in their thoughts and prayers during this challenging time.